name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
I also extended the State of Emergency for another 30 days as we continue to fight the spread of COVID-19. 

The days and weeks ahead will be difficult, but we all need to do our part by staying home and staying informed. For the latest DE updates, visit: http://de.gov/coronavirus

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
The science tells us that wearing a face covering in certain public settings can help prevent transmission and spread of the COVID-19 virus. But wearing a face covering is NOT an excuse to spend more time in public. 

More info on face covering guidance:  https://coronavirus.delaware.gov/guidance-for-face-coverings/ … pic.twitter.com/38UzCS4ZVk

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
DE's response to COVID-19 has been driven by science, and will continue to be driven by science. 

Our goals:
—prevent a surge in cases
—protect hospital capacity
—save lives

name: DHSS
tweet: @JohnCarneyDE says "the next two weeks are really critical to our state" in terms of positive cases, hospitalizations and managing capacity at the state's hospitals. #StayHomeDE #StayHome #coronavirusDE pic.twitter.com/m5sqVnSe9t – at Carvel State Office Building

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
Delawareans also should not go out in public unnecessarily.

Stay safe. Stay home. Protect your neighbors.

We’ll get through this – but it’s going to take all of us.

#StayHomeDE

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
We are also:
• placing additional restrictions on businesses
• banning door-to-door solicitation
• closing pawn shops, video game stores, and other electronics retailers.

This is not the time for a vacation or tax-free shopping in Delaware.

tweet: Thank you @WSmallwood28 for helping us share the #StayHomeDE message.

tweet:

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:

➡️ For more info on our latest order: https://news.delaware.gov/2020/04/02/governor-carney-urges-delawareans-businesses-nonprofits-to-support-covid-19-response/ …

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
Our goal is to save lives. This is a serious situation & we need everyone to cooperate. Don’t go out in public unnecessarily. If you need to go out, stay away from others. Wash your hands & follow basic hygiene guidance. 

We’ll get through this, but it’s going to take all of us.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
Our order limits public gatherings to 10 people through May 15, or until the public health threat has been eliminated.

And businesses that remain open are required to take new action to enforce social distancing. Learn about the steps here: https://news.delaware.gov/2020/04/01/governor-carney-restricts-gatherings-requires-businesses-to-strictly-comply-with-social-distancing/ …

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
This is a serious situation. Violating an emergency order is a criminal offense. We need everyone to do their part. 

Stay home. 

Protect your neighbors.

Stay informed:  http://de.gov/coronavirus

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
We’re doing everything we can do to slow the spread. We’re asking all of you to do your part by taking this threat seriously and following the guidance we’ve issued to stay at home. 

We must protect those who are most vulnerable to the threat of COVID-19.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: This is a sad day, and this is a scary time. Please, please, take this threat seriously— and do your part to stem the spread of COVID-19.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: Thank you to the health care workers who are putting their health and safety on the line to protect ours.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: The additional protections in this updated order are essential to help support Delawareans– especially our most vulnerable neighbors–as this situation evolves.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
To all of Delaware’s health care workers who are on the front lines of our response: thank you. 

We owe you all a debt of gratitude.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:

We’ll get through this, but we all need to pitch in and take this threat seriously.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: Starting tomorrow (3/18) at 8:00 am, bowling alleys, concert events, movie theaters, sports facilities, fitness centers, and health spas must cease operations to prevent the spread of coronavirus in DE.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
Restaurants are part of the spirit of our community. We can take basic health precautions and still support them during this challenging time. We’ll get through this! 

Stay informed:  http://de.gov/coronavirus

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
If you gather with 50+ people, you are only increasing the risk that more Delawareans will come in contact with coronavirus. 

Let’s not make a challenging situation worse.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
Restaurants also remain a critical source of food for vulnerable populations. 

But this is a very serious situation, with a significant amount of uncertainty.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet:
What you can do to help stop the spread of coronavirus:

☑️ Practice social distancing
☑️ Wash your hands
☑️ Stay home as much as possible

We will get through this - and the precautionary actions you take will help.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: We will be working with districts to plan for providing learning opportunities and other meal and social services for our students in the event of an extended closure.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: Delaware children deserve a world-class education, and ongoing access to services that are delivered in our schools each day. Many students – especially those from disadvantaged communities – also rely on school meals for nutrition, and other important social services.
